# Cursor Rules for AI2AIM RX Platform

## Project Context
This is a medical RX management platform built with Next.js 14+, TypeScript, Supabase, and AI agents.

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Prefer functional components with hooks
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Follow Next.js App Router conventions
- Use shadcn/ui components when available

## File Organization
- Components in `src/components/`
- Business logic in `src/lib/`
- Types in `src/types/`
- Hooks in `src/hooks/`
- API routes in `src/app/api/`

## Medical Domain
- Always consider HIPAA compliance
- Validate all medical data inputs
- Use proper error handling for sensitive operations
- Log all actions for audit trails

## AI Agents
- All agents extend BaseAgent
- Use agent registry for agent management
- Implement proper error handling
- Log all agent interactions

## Database
- Use Supabase client/server utilities
- Always use RLS policies
- Validate data before database operations
- Use transactions for multi-step operations

## Testing
- Write tests for critical business logic
- Test AI agent interactions
- Test automation workflows
- Test authentication flows
